      <abstract>
        <p>Oxo's new scoop for impatient ice cream lovers noted; photo (Food Stuff column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Ice-cream lovers can be an impatient lot, in a hurry to get the sweet stuff into a dish or cone. Oxo's new scoop makes the job easier: when the lever on the handle is pressed, the ice cream pops right out of the brushed-stainless-steel bowl. As on all Oxo kitchen tools, the handle is cushioned. The scoop is $11.50 at Broadway Panhandler, 477 Broome Street (Greene Street), and other housewares stores.</p>
      </block>
